name: Trebor
description: a tall, muscled man with a wide grin.

49: He squints at you. "We've met, haven't we?"
"Hello," he says, lumbering over to you and extending a large hand.
"Sorry, I sold you my last ship."
"Sorry, I sold you my last skiff."
"I used to sell ships and skiffs."
"So long friend." He lumbers back to his work.
892: $N turns to $Y. "It'll cost you #4 gold for the deed. Interested?"
1302: "Excellent!" After accepting the gold, $N hands $Y the deed.
1462: Your party takes up a collection to purchase the vessel.
